result.execSummary:
Christopher Cochran was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Christopher Cochran was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Christopher Cochran not in court.  Carole R Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant has been turned over to the State of North Carolina. 
On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant Christopher Cochran in court with attorney Anne A. Devitt.  Defendant Christopher Cochran in custody.  Carole R. Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Witkowiak, Branch 22.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of North Carolina.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant remanded into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Status conference scheduled for April 29, 2014 at 08:30 am.
